<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-011-078  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 011 078.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Jan 1 1990 v11 n1 p7(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC dons price cap for major LECs starting in 1991. (FederalCommunications Commission; local-exchange carriers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Thyfault, Mary E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission will change its pricingpolicy with local-exchange carriers (LEC), replacing its current12 percent rate-of-return pricing for major carriers with pricecaps beginning in Jan 1991.andP;  Large LECs with over $100 million inannual revenues will automatically be placed under a price capregulation, while smaller companies will remain under therate-of-return pricing, unless individual companies prefer pricecaps.andP;  Critics say that the rate-of-return policy does notencourage cost-cutting measures or innovation because profits stayfixed at a certain level.andP;  Price caps would keep a ceiling onrates that can be charged by carriers, and more efficiency wouldbring higher profit margins for regional Bell companies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionPricing PolicyTelephone CompaniesBell Regional Holding CompaniesTelecommunicationsGovernment RegulationProfit Margin.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>